1088
00:53:19,330 --> 00:53:21,960
When I was a teenager,

1089
00:53:22,000 --> 00:53:24,900
my... my mother

1090
00:53:24,930 --> 00:53:27,600
worked in a department store
refolding merchandise

1091
00:53:27,630 --> 00:53:29,960
at night after
everyone had gone home.

1092
00:53:32,000 --> 00:53:34,400
She didn't even feel bad.

1093
00:53:34,430 --> 00:53:36,530
Just a little pain
under her arm.

1094
00:53:38,760 --> 00:53:41,330
Ignored it for the longest time.

1095
00:53:41,360 --> 00:53:43,300
Store insisted she see someone.

1096
00:53:43,330 --> 00:53:45,330
And then, six weeks later...

1097
00:53:48,260 --> 00:53:51,760
I do believe that's
the last time I ever cried.

1098
00:53:51,800 --> 00:53:53,800
Got a life's worth of tears out.

1099
00:53:58,330 --> 00:53:59,500
You come all this way

1100
00:53:59,530 --> 00:54:02,230
just to give me that
swell-looking balloon?

1101
