1120
00:54:59,000 --> 00:55:01,460
We passed
in the hall.

1121
00:55:01,500 --> 00:55:04,200
She was going home to clean up,

1122
00:55:04,230 --> 00:55:06,000
call relatives.

1123
00:55:06,030 --> 00:55:08,800
It just poured off her.

1124
00:55:08,830 --> 00:55:10,730
"I love this man.

1125
00:55:10,760 --> 00:55:13,460
"I'm so angry at this man.

1126
00:55:13,500 --> 00:55:14,660
"I love this man.

1127
00:55:14,700 --> 00:55:17,700
I am so angry at this man."

1128
00:55:26,530 --> 00:55:28,530
ALLISON:
Thank you.

1129
00:55:37,130 --> 00:55:40,000
They smashed their way
through this door.

1130
00:55:40,030 --> 00:55:42,500
Who, the cartoon bad guys?

1131
00:55:42,530 --> 00:55:44,200
It's an old,
rotted doorjamb,

1132
00:55:44,230 --> 00:55:46,430
an old, rotted door.

1133
00:55:46,460 --> 00:55:48,900
If she didn't have it locked,
didn't have the chain on it,

1134
00:55:48,930 --> 00:55:49,930
you could kick this open,

1135
00:55:49,960 --> 00:55:52,000
we'd never even know.

1136
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:01,260
What is it we're
looking for again?

1137
00:56:01,300 --> 00:56:04,960
I don't know, a reason why
killers who hit wealthy families

1138
00:56:05,000 --> 00:56:06,700
for no reason at all
would also kill

1139
00:56:06,730 --> 00:56:09,100
a substitute teacher
and her child.

1140
00:56:14,480 --> 00:56:17,480
SCANLON:
Methinks the woman
liked to paint.

1141
00:56:28,110 --> 00:56:28,680
Look at this.

1142
00:56:28,680 --> 00:56:30,710
It looks like she's trying
to learn how to paint

1143
00:56:30,750 --> 00:56:32,280
in the style
of this artist.

1144
00:56:38,480 --> 00:56:40,250
Do these look familiar?

1145
00:56:40,280 --> 00:56:42,710
Sure. I'd recognize
that squiggle anywhere.

1146
00:56:42,750 --> 00:56:44,280
It's after
5:00, Allison.

1147
00:56:44,310 --> 00:56:46,650
We've got at least a
two-hour drive back.

1148
00:56:46,680 --> 00:56:48,550
Allison?

1149
00:56:50,550 --> 00:56:54,210
The food court at the mall?

1150
00:56:54,250 --> 00:56:56,510
You can have dinner
anywhere you want,

1151
00:56:56,550 --> 00:56:59,250
and you want to have it
at the food court at the mall?

1152
00:56:59,280 --> 00:57:01,810
Daddy, if you don't really
want to know, you shouldn't ask.

1153
00:57:01,850 --> 00:57:03,810
What's wrong with the
food court at the mall?

1154
00:57:03,850 --> 00:57:05,050
They have everything.

1155
00:57:05,080 --> 00:57:07,210
They have food from
all over the world.

1156
00:57:07,250 --> 00:57:10,110
Okay, the people have spoken.

1157
00:57:10,150 --> 00:57:11,750
Let me just get
out of these clothes,

1158
00:57:11,780 --> 00:57:13,580
and we'll head out to the mall.

1159
00:57:13,610 --> 00:57:15,710
Yippee.

1160
00:57:33,380 --> 00:57:34,450
Hello?

1161
00:57:43,850 --> 00:57:45,850
