that's out of the ordinary?

1188
00:59:03,680 --> 00:59:04,850
I don't know.

1189
00:59:04,880 --> 00:59:07,750
Did Mommy get a new
bedspread or something?

1190
00:59:09,750 --> 00:59:11,280
Huh.

1191
00:59:14,480 --> 00:59:15,680
It's the wind, Daddy.

1192
00:59:20,380 --> 00:59:22,080
It's just the wind.

1193
00:59:22,110 --> 00:59:24,310
Huh.

1194
00:59:24,350 --> 00:59:25,610
I'm really hungry.

1195
00:59:25,650 --> 00:59:27,250
We're all
really hungry.

1196
00:59:27,280 --> 00:59:28,250
Yes, me, too.

1197
00:59:28,280 --> 00:59:29,610
Come on.

1198
00:59:29,650 --> 00:59:32,650
I'll change later.
Let's get out of here.

1199
00:59:32,680 --> 00:59:34,050
Let's go.

1200
00:59:35,660 --> 00:59:37,760
6

1201
01:00:00,360 --> 01:00:02,530
Look at this.
Together again.

1202
01:00:08,430 --> 01:00:10,400
If we're here,
who's running the city?

1203
01:00:12,530 --> 01:00:14,760
Could you have picked
a more out of the way place?

1204
01:00:14,800 --> 01:00:17,360
Yeah, pretty
obscure, huh?

1205
01:00:18,250 --> 01:00:20,080
May I start you off
with something to drink?

1206
01:00:20,110 --> 01:00:21,550
You on the clock?

1207
01:00:21,580 --> 01:00:23,110
I'll have a scotch
and soda.

1208
01:00:23,150 --> 01:00:26,850
The lady will have
a dirty martini.

1209
01:00:26,880 --> 01:00:29,310
So, when last we spoke, uh...

1210
01:00:29,350 --> 01:00:30,650
DINOVI:
When last we spoke...

1211
01:00:31,210 --> 01:00:33,010
Where do I start?

1212
01:00:33,050 --> 01:00:35,710
Drinks... Lady from
the third district...

1213
01:00:35,750 --> 01:00:37,150
It went great.

1214
01:00:37,180 --> 01:00:39,250
It's been 24 hours, and
I still don't believe it.

1215
01:00:39,280 --> 01:00:40,280
Believe what?

1216
01:00:42,310 --> 01:00:44,450
They want me to run
for city council.

1217
01:00:47,650 --> 01:00:48,850
(exhales)
I should cancel the cocktails

1218
01:00:48,880 --> 01:00:50,280
and get us
a bottle of champagne.

1219
01:00:50,310 --> 01:00:51,510
Don't do that.
I've been dreaming

1220
01:00:51,550 --> 01:00:52,610
about a martini all day.

1221
01:00:52,650 --> 01:00:53,910
A martini? Not me?

1222
01:00:53,950 --> 01:00:55,250
A martini and you.

1223
01:00:55,280 --> 01:00:56,910
I was just

1224
01:00:56,950 --> 01:00:59,450
so completely
taken by surprise.

1225
01:00:59,480 --> 01:01:01,250
Then they started hitting
me with questions.

1226
01:01:01,280 --> 01:01:03,480
Questions?

1227
01:01:03,510 --> 01:01:05,510
"Where were you born?
Are you a native?

1228
01:01:05,550 --> 01:01:06,750
"Do you belong
to any clubs?

1229
01:01:06,780 --> 01:01:07,780
Are you involved
with anyone?"

1230
01:01:07,810 --> 01:01:09,080
You fess up?

1231
01:01:09,110 --> 01:01:11,110
I told them the truth.

1232
01:01:11,150 --> 01:01:13,050
That, for all intents
and purposes, I'm...

1233
01:01:13,080 --> 01:01:14,780
You're at my house
one or two nights a week.

1234
01:01:14,810 --> 01:01:16,580
Well, no, I didn't
tell them that.

1235
01:01:16,610 --> 01:01:18,680
I don't think a woman
running for office

1236
01:01:18,680 --> 01:01:20,410
should be bragging about
making the walk of shame

1237
01:01:20,450 --> 01:01:22,680
from her lover's apartment to
her car at 6:30 in the morning,

1238
01:01:22,710 --> 01:01:25,550
praying that nobody sees her.

1239
01:01:25,580 --> 01:01:27,150
Yeah, well...

1240
01:01:28,810 --> 01:01:30,810
...I want to talk to you
about that.

1241
01:01:30,810 --> 01:01:32,580
No, it's okay.

1242
01:01:32,610 --> 01:01:33,950
I realized something.

1243
01:01:33,980 --> 01:01:36,480
I like what we have,
the way we have it.

1244
01:01:38,680 --> 01:01:40,750
I wasn't sure
at first.

1245
01:01:40,750 --> 01:01:43,180
Never been with someone who
didn't want to come home with me

1246
01:01:43,210 --> 01:01:44,980
to my folks at
Christmas, but...

1247
01:01:45,010 --> 01:01:45,980
but it's okay.

1248
01:01:46,010 --> 01:01:47,210
It's actually good.

1249
01:01:47,250 --> 01:01:50,250
One of the things these
people said to me was,

1250
01:01:50,280 --> 01:01:52,010
I guess a lot of the
union agreements--

1251
01:01:52,050 --> 01:01:56,010
police, fire, teachers--
they're all coming up next year.

1252
01:01:56,050 --> 01:02:00,210
I mean, the last thing they
wanted to hear was that I'm--

1253
01:02:00,250 --> 01:02:04,480
whatever you call this thing we
have-- with a civil servant.

1254
01:02:09,380 --> 01:02:11,050
Is that what I am,
a civil servant?

1255
01:02:11,080 --> 01:02:12,780
What? No.

1256
01:02:12,810 --> 01:02:14,210
That's their word.

1257
01:02:14,250 --> 01:02:15,250
It's really just about...

1258
01:02:15,280 --> 01:02:16,510
I get the point.

1259
01:02:17,130 --> 01:02:18,700
They don't want you
sleeping with the help.

1260
01:02:18,730 --> 01:02:20,630
It's really just about
these negotiations.

1261
01:02:20,660 --> 01:02:21,930
What did you say?

1262
01:02:21,960 --> 01:02:24,810
(cell phone ringing)
There was nothing to say.

1263
01:02:30,080 --> 01:02:31,110
Got it.

1264
01:02:31,150 --> 01:02:33,480
I'll see you there.

1265
01:02:34,760 --> 01:02:35,900
Wait a second.

1266
01:02:35,900 --> 01:02:37,130
I thought we were having dinner.

1267
01:02:37,160 --> 01:02:38,310
Look, I don't know
what to tell you.

1268
01:02:38,310 --> 01:02:39,950
I'm just a civil servant.

1269
01:02:39,980 --> 01:02:42,050
I get a call, I go to work.

1270
01:02:42,080 --> 01:02:43,950
Lee...
What?

1271
01:02:45,280 --> 01:02:48,060
Hey, some people just got shot
to death in Hasbrook Heights.

1272
01:02:48,060 --> 01:02:49,180
The mayor's back in town,

1273
01:02:49,180 --> 01:02:50,780
so you're not
getting the call,

1274
01:02:50,810 --> 01:02:52,210
but I'm just a working guy.

1275
01:02:52,250 --> 01:02:54,210
Enjoy your drink; it's paid for.

1276
01:02:54,250 --> 01:02:56,350
Are you hurt?

1277
01:02:56,380 --> 01:02:59,380
You don't even let me keep
a toothbrush at your place

1278
01:02:59,410 --> 01:03:01,380
and you're hurt?!

1279
01:03:01,410 --> 01:03:02,880
I'm not hurt.

1280
01:03:02,910 --> 01:03:03,880
I'm thrilled for you.

1281
01:03:03,910 --> 01:03:05,980
You have my vote.

1282
01:03:06,010 --> 01:03:08,380
But I got to go.

1283
01:03:12,810 --> 01:03:14,810
Will the gentleman
be returning?

1284
01:03:21,050 --> 01:03:23,050
It's Scanlon.
He says it's important.

1285
01:03:23,480 --> 01:03:26,850
You didn't have another
bad dream, did you?

1286
01:03:29,750 --> 01:03:31,480
Hello?

1287
01:03:31,510 --> 01:03:34,110
SCANLON:
You want the good news, the bad
news or the very bad news?

1288
01:03:34,150 --> 01:03:35,910
Just tell me
what's going on.

1289
01:03:35,950 --> 01:03:38,410
(over phone):
Another home invasion.

1290
01:03:38,450 --> 01:03:41,010
Only this time, the homeowner
was packing heat.

1291
01:03:41,050 --> 01:03:42,950
Killed all three of them.

1292
01:03:42,980 --> 01:03:44,180
I think it's over, Allison.

1293
01:03:44,210 --> 01:03:45,880
I think it's all over.

1294
01:03:45,910 --> 01:03:47,380
Okay.

1295
01:03:47,410 --> 01:03:49,850
What about the very bad news?

1296
01:03:49,880 --> 01:03:51,580
Your boss is still
in the hospital.

1297
01:03:51,610 --> 01:03:53,450
I need you to get dressed
and come downtown

1298
01:03:53,480 --> 01:03:55,180
