1305
01:04:03,480 --> 01:04:05,880
They're not gonna bother
anybody anymore.

1306
01:04:05,910 --> 01:04:08,910
SCANLON:
Spell your name
for me, please.

1307
01:04:08,950 --> 01:04:10,450
Alan Gardner.

1308
01:04:10,480 --> 01:04:12,950
G-A-R-D-N-E-R.

1309
01:04:12,980 --> 01:04:14,450
And I should warn you,

1310
01:04:14,480 --> 01:04:15,710
I don't think
I'm actually sick, but I...

1311
01:04:15,710 --> 01:04:16,260
We know.

1312
01:04:16,260 --> 01:04:18,330
We know that you've been through
a lot tonight.

1313
01:04:18,810 --> 01:04:21,250
The officer mentioned
that you've been throwing up.

1314
01:04:23,980 --> 01:04:25,800
I think it's just nerves.

1315
01:04:25,800 --> 01:04:27,630
I'm actually feeling
a little better right now.

1316
01:04:29,660 --> 01:04:31,400
You want to tell
us what happened?

1317
01:04:31,430 --> 01:04:33,760
What happened...

1318
01:04:33,800 --> 01:04:36,300
I don't know...
I mean, I guess,

1319
01:04:36,330 --> 01:04:39,430
like everybody with a big
house, I've been on edge.

1320
01:04:39,460 --> 01:04:41,560
It was the staff's
night off.

1321
01:04:41,600 --> 01:04:42,600
I had been reading.

1322
01:04:42,630 --> 01:04:45,160
Fell asleep in bed.

1323
01:04:45,200 --> 01:04:46,260
Then the alarm went off.

1324
01:04:46,300 --> 01:04:48,200
What did you do?

1325
01:04:48,230 --> 01:04:50,100
I ran into the closet.

1326
01:04:50,130 --> 01:04:52,860
It's like a little
vault, actually--

1327
01:04:52,900 --> 01:04:55,230
fireproof.

1328
01:04:55,260 --> 01:04:58,700
I keep some papers there,
antiquities, canvases.

1329
01:04:58,730 --> 01:05:00,430
I'm an art dealer.

1330
01:05:00,460 --> 01:05:03,100
And I thought, well, I'll just
lock the door and stay in here.

1331
01:05:03,130 --> 01:05:04,730
I don't think they can
shoot through it.

1332
01:05:04,760 --> 01:05:06,060
Like a panic room.

1333
01:05:06,100 --> 01:05:07,060
Yeah.

1334
01:05:07,100 --> 01:05:08,060
But small.

1335
01:05:08,100 --> 01:05:09,160
And there's monitors in there.

1336
01:05:09,200 --> 01:05:11,400
So I can see them moving
through the house.

1337
01:05:11,430 --> 01:05:13,300
And I know the police
are trying to call.

1338
01:05:13,330 --> 01:05:16,600
And I thought for a moment,

1339
01:05:16,630 --> 01:05:19,360
I think I might actually
live through this thing.

1340
01:05:23,300 --> 01:05:25,260
Then they shot Keezey.

1341
01:05:29,330 --> 01:05:32,300
That little schnauzer
is the only family I have.

1342
01:05:35,100 --> 01:05:37,800
I mean, you go through
the housebreaking,

1343
01:05:37,830 --> 01:05:41,860
the bladder infections,
the doggie tumors,

1344
01:05:41,900 --> 01:05:43,900
and you just never imagine...

1345
01:05:46,800 --> 01:05:48,260
Even on the
black-and-white monitor,

1346
01:05:48,300 --> 01:05:50,460
I can see him lying there,

1347
01:05:50,500 --> 01:05:51,900
the blood coming
out of his body.

1348
01:05:55,830 --> 01:05:59,200
That's when I saw the gun...

1349
01:05:59,230 --> 01:06:02,660
the rifle, box of ammo...

1350
01:06:02,700 --> 01:06:04,400
I got it, like,
six years ago,

1351
01:06:04,430 --> 01:06:07,160
to go skeet shooting with
a client, which I hated.

1352
01:06:07,200 --> 01:06:09,830
So much noise, and it...

1353
01:06:09,860 --> 01:06:11,830
hurt my shoulder.

1354
01:06:16,330 --> 01:06:18,200
Then I went out
into the hall.

1355
01:06:20,230 --> 01:06:22,660
The way the stairs work,
you can't see into the hall

1356
01:06:22,700 --> 01:06:25,200
unless you're at the top.

1357
01:06:27,230 --> 01:06:29,460
And I just waited.

1358
01:06:29,500 --> 01:06:31,700
(gunshots)

1359
01:06:42,430 --> 01:06:43,400
(gently):
Mr. Gardner?

1360
01:06:43,430 --> 01:06:46,930
I am a civilized person.

1361
01:06:46,960 --> 01:06:48,660
I know they were killers.

1362
01:06:48,700 --> 01:06:50,160
They killed my Keezey.

1363
01:06:50,200 --> 01:06:53,860
But I just never imagined,
in the course of my life,

1364
01:06:53,900 --> 01:06:57,000
that I would actually
kill another man.

1365
01:06:59,530 --> 01:07:01,530
Three other men.

1366
01:07:03,660 --> 01:07:06,100
I think I'm gonna be sick.

1367
01:07:19,230 --> 01:07:22,460
Look who's returning
to the marital bed.

1368
01:07:24,500 --> 01:07:28,100
What is it, like,
4:00 in the morning?

1369
01:07:28,130 --> 01:07:30,200
It's nice of you to
make an appearance.

1370
01:07:30,230 --> 01:07:31,560
It's, like, 5:00.

1371
01:07:31,600 --> 01:07:33,900
Or five-oh-s...

1372
01:07:34,960 --> 01:07:36,360
...seven.

1373
01:07:45,200 --> 01:07:48,060
I think it's really over.

1374
01:07:48,100 --> 01:07:51,100
The home invaders are dead.

1375
01:07:51,130 --> 01:07:54,100
This meek little
art dealer shot them

1376
01:07:54,130 --> 01:07:58,130
'cause they killed his dog.

1377
01:07:58,160 --> 01:08:01,200
Bridgette will be relieved.

1378
01:08:01,230 --> 01:08:04,360
No more bad dreams.

1379
01:08:04,400 --> 01:08:07,400
It's funny the way
stuff happens.

1380
01:08:10,800 --> 01:08:15,000
I think your boyfriend's
gone, by the way.

1381
01:08:15,030 --> 01:08:16,600
ALLISON:
Oh, yeah?

1382
01:08:16,630 --> 01:08:18,500
JOE:
We had a chat.

1383
01:08:18,530 --> 01:08:20,960
I mean, I had a chat.

1384
01:08:21,000 --> 01:08:23,300
And I think
he heard it,

1385
01:08:23,330 --> 01:08:25,660
because I haven't felt
any cold breezes,

1386
01:08:25,700 --> 01:08:28,660
and he hasn't
been seen since.

1387
01:08:28,700 --> 01:08:30,460
What do you mean?

1388
01:08:30,500 --> 01:08:32,200
Seen by who?
Who could see him?

1389
01:08:32,230 --> 01:08:33,300
He's a ghost.

1390
01:08:33,330 --> 01:08:35,700
I had Ariel take a
little look for him.

1391
01:08:35,730 --> 01:08:38,330
I mean, she didn't know

1392
01:08:38,360 --> 01:08:39,830
that that's who she
was looking for.

1393
01:08:39,860 --> 01:08:41,830
You did not.
Yes...

1394
01:08:45,400 --> 01:08:47,700
I certainly did.

1395
01:08:47,730 --> 01:08:51,030
Did you think I was just gonna
give you up without a fight?

1396
01:08:54,500 --> 01:08:57,500
I love you with
all my heart.

1397
01:09:35,930 --> 01:09:37,160
You got it now?

1398
01:09:37,200 --> 01:09:39,230
You got it figured out?
'Cause I got to go.

1399
01:09:46,630 --> 01:09:47,830
SCANLON:
Wow, what are you doing here?

1400
01:09:47,860 --> 01:09:49,460
Aren't you the lady
who was with me

1401
01:09:49,500 --> 01:09:51,160
till almost 4:30 this morning?

1402
01:09:51,200 --> 01:09:52,730
Shouldn't you be
at home sleeping?

1403
01:09:52,760 --> 01:09:55,730
I tried sleeping.

1404
01:09:55,760 --> 01:09:57,530
I kept dreaming.

1405
01:09:57,560 --> 01:09:59,560
What about you?
Why aren't you home sleeping?

1406
01:09:59,600 --> 01:10:00,660
I don't know.

1407
01:10:00,700 --> 01:10:02,460
Phone kept ringing.

1408
01:10:02,500 --> 01:10:04,760
You wanted to see me.
Is something up?

1409
01:10:04,800 --> 01:10:07,260
It's like I said,
I keep having dreams.

1410
01:10:07,300 --> 01:10:09,430
Yeah? So?

1411
01:10:09,460 --> 01:10:13,300
Isn't that kind of like Einstein
always having brainstorms?

1412
01:10:13,330 --> 01:10:14,330
You recognize this?

1413
01:10:14,360 --> 01:10:15,360
Thought you said
you would

1414
01:10:15,400 --> 01:10:16,600
recognize this
squiggle anywhere.

1415
01:10:16,630 --> 01:10:19,160
It's that painting Devalos
told us was so valuable,

1416
01:10:19,200 --> 01:10:21,630
that was hanging
at the first house.

1417
01:10:21,630 --> 01:10:23,730
Okay.
Remember

1418
01:10:23,760 --> 01:10:26,630
those little paintings at Olga's
house I was looking at--

1419
01:10:26,660 --> 01:10:27,930
I told you they reminded me
of something?

1420
01:10:27,930 --> 01:10:30,500
This is the painting
they remind me of.

1421
01:10:30,530 --> 01:10:32,900
I'm glad we, uh,
solved that mystery.
I think she was

1422
01:10:32,930 --> 01:10:35,360
trying to learn how to paint
in the style of this painter.

1423
01:10:35,400 --> 01:10:39,430
I think she was trying to learn
to paint this painting.

1424
01:10:39,460 --> 01:10:41,230
You think they killed her
for that?

1425
01:10:41,260 --> 01:10:42,830
How does that explain
the other killings?

1426
01:10:42,860 --> 01:10:45,730
How does that explain the home
invasions in two other states?

1427
01:10:45,760 --> 01:10:48,460
To be honest, I don't know.
I just...

1428
01:10:48,500 --> 01:10:51,400
Both those houses are still
crime scenes, right?

1429
01:10:51,430 --> 01:10:53,560
Could someone possibly

1430
01:10:53,600 --> 01:10:55,660
just bring me this painting?

1431
01:10:55,700 --> 01:10:58,260
Maybe all the little ones
I was looking at

1432
01:10:58,300 --> 01:10:59,700
at Olga's house?
Allison, is it possible

1433
01:10:59,730 --> 01:11:02,030
that in all the hubbub last
night, that you missed the part

1434
01:11:02,060 --> 01:11:03,560
where the home invaders
were shot to death?

1435
01:11:03,600 --> 01:11:04,900
No, I heard that.

1436
01:11:04,930 --> 01:11:06,800
Did you miss the part
where I said
(phone rings)

1437
01:11:06,830 --> 01:11:08,900
I was still having
dreams about it all?

1438
01:11:12,160 --> 01:11:13,300
So what do you think?

1439
01:11:15,830 --> 01:11:17,810
I think someone's in a mood.

1440
01:11:17,810 --> 01:11:19,380
Sorry.

1441
01:11:19,410 --> 01:11:22,680
A friend of mine who was
visiting left suddenly.

1442
01:11:22,710 --> 01:11:24,210
I guess...

1443
01:11:24,250 --> 01:11:27,150
I guess I wanted to say good-bye
more than I realized.

1444
01:11:27,180 --> 01:11:29,380
Yeah, good-byes are
a bitch, aren't they.

1445
01:11:29,410 --> 01:11:30,410
WOMAN:
How's your vision?

1446
01:11:30,410 --> 01:11:31,380
It's good.

1447
01:11:31,410 --> 01:11:32,350
I can see perfectly.

1448
01:11:32,380 --> 01:11:33,680
I feel good, too.

1449
01:11:33,710 --> 01:11:35,410
Frankly, Doctor, I feel ready
to get out of here.

1450
01:11:35,450 --> 01:11:36,710
Ready to get back to work.

1451
01:11:36,750 --> 01:11:38,580
Well, that's what's going
to kill you, you know.

1452
01:11:38,610 --> 01:11:39,710
How good you feel.

1453
01:11:39,750 --> 01:11:43,410
You have diabetes,
Mr. District Attorney.

1454
01:11:43,450 --> 01:11:45,510
I think that you've probably
had it for years,

1455
01:11:45,510 --> 01:11:46,610
but you just didn't know.

1456
01:11:46,650 --> 01:11:48,450
It's a sneaky little bastard.

1457
01:11:48,480 --> 01:11:50,080
If you're not checking for it,

1458
01:11:50,110 --> 01:11:52,550
it doesn't let you know it's
there until it's good and ready

1459
01:11:52,580 --> 01:11:54,550
to give you a stroke
or a heart attack,

1460
01:11:55,030 --> 01:11:56,760
make you impotent
or strike you blind.

1461
01:11:56,800 --> 01:11:59,230
Are you trying to frighten me?

1462
01:11:59,260 --> 01:12:01,030
No, I am trying
to warn you.

1463
01:12:01,060 --> 01:12:03,100
Now, I can see you
every three months.

1464
01:12:03,130 --> 01:12:04,230
We can monitor this thing.

1465
01:12:04,260 --> 01:12:06,500
I can teach you how to get
on top of it.

1466
01:12:06,530 --> 01:12:08,560
Or I can see you
in a couple of years.

1467
01:12:08,600 --> 01:12:11,430
Now, if they manage to keep
you alive until you get

1468
01:12:11,460 --> 01:12:13,200
to the hospital,
well, then we can

1469
01:12:13,230 --> 01:12:15,960
chat about how high on your leg
we need to amputate

1470
01:12:16,000 --> 01:12:17,660
or maybe
where the best Braille

1471
01:12:17,700 --> 01:12:19,860
classes are.

1472
01:12:33,500 --> 01:12:34,960
Okay, so what
does this prove?

1473
01:12:35,000 --> 01:12:37,030
You know, I don't know anything
about this stuff, Allison.

1474
01:12:37,060 --> 01:12:38,500
Yeah, I know. Me neither.

1475
01:12:38,530 --> 01:12:40,760
But I know someone who does.

1476
01:12:40,800 --> 01:12:42,400
Hey, I just wanted
to let you know

1477
01:12:42,430 --> 01:12:43,560
I'm heading out to Carefree.

1478
01:12:43,600 --> 01:12:45,260
Paying a visit to Alan Gardner.

1479
01:12:45,300 --> 01:12:48,260
That gallery owner who shot
those three home invaders.

1480
01:12:48,300 --> 01:12:49,630
Are you okay to drive?

1481
01:12:49,660 --> 01:12:52,130
What'd you get,
about 15 minutes sleep?

1482
01:12:52,160 --> 01:12:53,700
No, I'm fine.

1483
01:12:53,730 --> 01:12:55,130
I'm not going to be there long.

1484
01:12:55,160 --> 01:12:57,030
I've just have a couple
paintings in the car

1485
01:12:57,060 --> 01:12:59,130
I asked him to take a look at.

1486
01:12:59,160 --> 01:13:01,860
Hey, can I ask you something?

1487
01:13:01,900 --> 01:13:03,500
Hmm? Sure.

1488
01:13:03,530 --> 01:13:05,000
What did you say to him?

1489
01:13:05,030 --> 01:13:06,630
What are you talking about?

1490
01:13:06,660 --> 01:13:08,630
To Clay. Last night.

1491
01:13:12,100 --> 01:13:14,060
You know what?

1492
01:13:14,100 --> 01:13:16,000
I'm sorry I mentioned it.
It was silly.

1493
01:13:16,030 --> 01:13:17,760
I'm sure that
there was nobody there.

1494
01:13:18,800 --> 01:13:21,400
Okay. But what did you say
to him?

1495
01:13:25,560 --> 01:13:27,530
Hello?

1496
01:13:28,730 --> 01:13:30,900
CLAY:
He said, "She's mine."

1497
01:13:30,930 --> 01:13:34,800
He said everything
you'd want him to say.

1498
01:13:34,830 --> 01:13:37,800
He said everything
you'd hoped he'd say,

1499
01:13:37,830 --> 01:13:40,430
if some crazy numbskull
showed up on your doorstep

1500
01:13:40,460 --> 01:13:43,460
with the idea that maybe
he could have you back.

1501
01:13:51,330 --> 01:13:53,330
Sorry. I-I lost you.

1502
01:13:53,360 --> 01:13:57,430
Yeah, well, um, I don't know
what to tell you.

1503
01:13:57,460 --> 01:14:00,130
I don't know, exactly,

1504
01:14:00,160 --> 01:14:02,600
what I said, and I really
don't think it matters.

1505
01:14:02,630 --> 01:14:04,830
You're right.
It doesn't matter.

1506
01:14:04,860 --> 01:14:07,800
I mean, I don't know what I was
getting so worked up about.

1507
01:14:09,000 --> 01:14:12,800
After all... I'm here.

1508
01:14:12,830 --> 01:14:15,200
Till death do us part.

1509
01:14:15,230 --> 01:14:16,600
Yes.

1510
01:14:16,630 --> 01:14:19,430
And who knows.
Maybe longer.

1511
01:14:20,730 --> 01:14:22,130
I'll see you when I get home.

1512
01:14:22,160 --> 01:14:24,960
I will see you
when you get home.

1513
01:14:31,500 --> 01:14:33,260
He's a good man.

1514
01:14:35,330 --> 01:14:37,260
I know.

1515
01:14:37,300 --> 01:14:39,860
I was wrong
about why I'm here.

1516
01:14:39,900 --> 01:14:42,560
And you were right.

1517
01:14:42,600 --> 01:14:45,530
And I am smug, vain, selfish...

1518
01:14:45,560 --> 01:14:47,230
even in death.

1519
01:14:47,260 --> 01:14:50,830
None of this has anything
to do with me.

1520
01:14:50,860 --> 01:14:53,460
I finally figured that out
last night.

1521
01:14:53,500 --> 01:14:56,230
I'm not here to woo you.

1522
01:14:56,260 --> 01:14:58,830
I'm here to help you.

1523
01:14:58,860 --> 01:15:01,060
To tell you something

1524
01:15:01,100 --> 01:15:03,560
that you otherwise
wouldn't know.

1525
01:15:03,600 --> 01:15:06,160
To redeem myself.

1526
01:15:07,730 --> 01:15:12,830
And then, Allison,
I think I'll be on my way.

1527
01:15:12,860 --> 01:15:16,360
You sent me that dream
last night, didn't you?

1528
01:15:16,400 --> 01:15:17,400
The one with

1529
01:15:17,430 --> 01:15:19,730
the cartoon?

1530
01:15:19,760 --> 01:15:22,300
I know where you're going.

1531
01:15:22,330 --> 01:15:23,930
And I know what you're
about to do.

1532
01:15:23,960 --> 01:15:25,660
And I know how it all ends up.

1533
01:15:25,700 --> 01:15:28,830
But I need to get you
to do something first.

1534
01:15:39,530 --> 01:15:41,660
This is where
I'm supposed to be.

1535
01:15:41,700 --> 01:15:43,000
Mr. District Attorney,

1536
01:15:43,030 --> 01:15:44,800
I'd like to introduce
you to Alan Gardner.

1537
01:15:44,830 --> 01:15:46,360
The gentleman who
single-handedly stopped

1538
01:15:46,400 --> 01:15:47,660
those three ruthless
home invaders.

1539
01:15:47,700 --> 01:15:48,930
This is an honor,

1540
01:15:48,960 --> 01:15:50,900
sir.
No, it's an honor
meeting you, sir.

1541
01:15:50,930 --> 01:15:52,200
Please.

1542
01:15:52,230 --> 01:15:55,000
I apologize for not being made
available to you sooner.

1543
01:15:55,000 --> 01:15:56,500
I was a bit
under the weather.

1544
01:15:56,530 --> 01:15:58,960
But I just wanted you to know
that this office stands ready

1545
01:15:59,000 --> 01:16:01,060
to help you navigate whatever
legal hurdles your

1546
01:16:01,100 --> 01:16:02,230
extraordinarily brave actions

1547
01:16:02,260 --> 01:16:03,730
may have created
for you.

1548
01:16:04,260 --> 01:16:05,960
Oh.

1549
01:16:07,000 --> 01:16:08,110
Should I have brought

1550
01:16:08,110 --> 01:16:09,250
my lawyer?

1551
01:16:09,280 --> 01:16:11,010
Both the detective

1552
01:16:11,050 --> 01:16:12,280
and Mrs. Dubois,
the other night,

1553
01:16:12,310 --> 01:16:13,580
seemed to indicate
that... that...

1554
01:16:13,610 --> 01:16:14,910
That shooting
three people to death

1555
01:16:14,950 --> 01:16:16,310
to protect one's own life

1556
01:16:16,350 --> 01:16:18,650
is a perfectly justifiable
course of action? Absolutely.

