to our dreams.

1668
01:20:53,630 --> 01:20:57,400
And our dreams are the map
of our humanity.

1669
01:20:58,460 --> 01:21:00,560
Ever watch a child sleep?

1670
01:21:00,600 --> 01:21:03,160
They almost always smile.

1671
01:21:03,200 --> 01:21:06,200
They know what's coming.

1672
01:21:06,230 --> 01:21:07,730
And adults?

1673
01:21:07,760 --> 01:21:11,260
Ever notice how we try to tidy
up our lives just before bed?

1674
01:21:15,300 --> 01:21:17,200
Did you take your pills?

1675
01:21:19,330 --> 01:21:21,160
Check your sugar?

1676
01:21:26,760 --> 01:21:30,330
You die on me, I'll
never forgive you.

1677
01:21:30,360 --> 01:21:32,400
Don't worry.

1678
01:21:34,030 --> 01:21:36,130
I'm not going anywhere.

1679
01:21:41,430 --> 01:21:42,960
Or what a disappointment it is

1680
01:21:43,000 --> 01:21:44,700
when we're lurched out
of our sleep,

1681
01:21:44,730 --> 01:21:47,800
(phone rings)
or our dreams,
by something unexpected.

1682
01:21:51,400 --> 01:21:53,200
Scanlon.

1683
01:21:53,230 --> 01:21:55,160
Hi.

1684
01:21:58,000 --> 01:22:00,300
